  description="I love the combination of traditional Chinese elements with some postmodern concepts applied. The wood texture is beautifully done. At the center of the table, the calligraphy looks remarkably a real masterpiece in the joint-up style — I wonder if it was somehow transferred from a real work without losing the details. The Chinese characters are a poem by the celebrated Li Bai from China's Tang Dynasty: 危楼高百尺，手可摘星辰。不敢高声语，恐惊天上人。A verse about standing so high — at the balcony of a building perched on a mountain summit or perilous cliff — that the stars seem within reach. I dare not speak too loudly, for fear of startling the beings in the heavens."
